# Documentation Pattern Whitelist
# These patterns are intentionally used in documentation and should not be flagged as errors

## Valid Regex Patterns (Not broken references)
- /* ... */           # Code example placeholder pattern
- /AddressDataExtractor\./g  # Search pattern for refactoring documentation
- /<\w+/g            # HTML tag detection regex
- /throw new \w+\(/g # Error detection pattern  
- /async function \w+/g # Async function detection

## Valid Descriptive Text (Not file paths)
- "/src for library organization" # Describes directory purpose, not a link
- Directory structure explanations using path notation

## Guidelines for Documentation Tools
1. Exclude regex patterns (lines containing /pattern/flags) from link checking
2. Use context-aware parsing to distinguish file paths from descriptive text
3. Check for surrounding context (e.g., "explanation", "describes", "for")
4. Regex patterns typically contain special characters: \w, \., \(, etc.

